        <Document ID="20E6E60D-C314-4026-BC89-719BC2B1AAA0">
            <Title>Page 7: 2013</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;
PPANEL 1
SAUL and ISABEL stand at GRANDMOTHERS garden gate. GRANDMOTHER is in the foreground of the panel, bent low harvesting herbs in the garden. Half a dozen stringy black cats should also be visible in the panel - spread around. The GRANDMOTHER has not seen the two of them.
Panel 2
GRANDMOTHER is still bent low, facing the reader. Her head is still down. ISABEL is smiling. She knows her GRANDMOTHER is teasing SAUL. SAUL does not know this and looks a little unnerved.
GRANDMOTHER
So. You arrived then. Late, I see.
Panel 3
ISABEL is hugging her GRANDMOTHER. ISABEL is smiling widely. Her GRANDMOTHER is looking forbidding, but we can tell she is pleased to see ISABEL. She has a gentle hand on ISABELS cheek.
GRANDMOTHER (CONT'D)
That will do girl. Let me have a look at your man then.
Panel 4
GRANDMOTHER has her hand on SAULS cheek. Her thumb is dragging SAULS eye lid up and she is looking at SAULS white, bloodshot, eyeball very closely. SAUL looks non-plussed.
GRANDMOTHER (CONT'D)
Not ready yet.
Panel 5
GRANDMOTHER is checking SAULS teeth. She has both hands on SAULS face. Her index fingers are pushing SAULS top lip up. We see teeth and gums.
GRANDMOTHER (CONT'D)
Hmm...
Panel 6
The GRANDMOTHER is walking towards the reader. ISABEL and SAUL can be seen in the background of the panel. SAUL looks utterly confused. ISABEL looks unsettled. GRANDMOTHER looks grim faced and a little sad.
GRANDMOTHER (CONT'D)
Not ready. Not... at... all.
</Text>
