        <Document ID="C31615D2-D934-404B-9B5A-706FFD6D0C5E">
            <Title>Page 18: 2013</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

SAUL visits the bar on his own. He is chatting to a couple of the locals - who speak English. He is asking about the history of the village, any famous visitors (painters perhaps?) and ends by asking about the civil war. Atmosphere changes. Colder. No-one wants to talk about the civil war. SAUL apologises and changes the subject. </Text>
