        <Document ID="DD581132-0176-45CF-96C3-D9FD4DB018A1">
            <Title>Page 7: 2013</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

INTERIOR: 2013. DAY. CHAIN COFFEE SHOP. PHILIP AND ISABEL SIT AT A TABLE
SAUL
Black, no sugar. Is that OK?
ISABEL
Correcto.

PANEL 2

SAUL
Thanks for meeting me. I have some questions about the diary.

PANEL 3

ISABEL
Where does it come from?
SAUL
Yes. Predictable, I suppose.
ISABEL
It is my Grandmothers. She posted it to me last week, with a note asking me to give it to you.

PANEL 4

SAUL
Me? Specifically me? She had my address?
ISABEL
SÂ¡.
SAUL
How does your Grandmother know me?
ISABEL
I don't know. Until last week I knew nothing of the diary.

PANEL 5

ISABEL
I will ask her when I go home next week. We holiday.
SAUL
Can't you call her?
ISABEL
She has no phone. She is a woman of... tradition.

PANEL 6

SAUL
A neighbour?
ISABEL
There is no phone in the village. It is -
SAUL
- traditional?.

</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="96A326A8-82C1-4596-AE14-46566A588E89">
            <Title>Page 7: 1936</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

Outrage in village. Storm the Town Hall. Burn all landownership documents in the village square. Edward views it with amusement - the dead boy was nothing to him. The burning is futile.</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="30610BF6-8DB0-471D-86B0-4E3005F1F71C">
            <Title>Page 18: 1936</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

EXTERIOR: 1936. DAY. FOREST PATH. DEEP IN THE FOREST. EDWARD and the rest of the men are kneeling in the shadow of the trees at the edge of a clearing in the forest. They are all looking upwards into the sky. The men are dappled by the sunlight coming through through the tree foliage above them.

PANEL 2

CALVINO
The same?

SERGEANT
I believe so.

PANEL 3

RICHARD
Yes. You see the black discs on the wings? With the crosses? Edward, what are they called?

EDWARD
The crosses? St Andrews crosses. It's theirs... Definitely.

PANEL 4

EXTERIOR: 1936. DAY. THE SKY ABOVE THE FOREST. We see the underside of the bi-plane, (a Fokker VIIb3m - see http://www.zi.ku.dk/personal/drnash/model/spain/codes.html). It is set against a background of blue sky and clouds. No pilot is visible.

CALVINO
(off panel)
You think its something to do with that fascist patrol?

SERGEANT
(off panel)
It may be.

CALVINO
(off panel)
Looking just for us? The plane and the patrol? Both?

PANEL 5

EXTERIOR: 1936. DAY. FOREST PATH. DEEP IN THE FOREST. The men are looking at each other. They look solemn.

PANEL 6

CALVINO
Follando putas madres.
</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="90A340E8-6401-49DC-965F-5586B26F2916">
            <Title>Page 14: 2013</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;
PPANEL 1
EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. GRANDMOTHERS VINYARD.
SAUL and ISABEL stand between a long row of vines. They are in a field of vines - long symetrical parallel rows.
SAUL
Why did you leave, Isabel?
ISABEL
To live. To learn and see something of the world.
Panel 2
EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. SURROUNDING HILLS.
SAUL and ISABEL are walking in  the hills around the vilage. We can see the village - on its own hill - in the background. SAUL and ISABEL are walking a dirt track - leading upwards.
SAUL
You intend to come back after your medical training?
ISABEL
Of course. I have roots in the soil.
Panel 3
EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. FARM FIELD.
SAUL and ISABEL are crossing a farmers field. The field is full of sheep. They are walking towards the village, which we can see - up on its hill - in the background.
SAUL
This would be a wonderful place to paint. Did I tell you I am an Art Historian?
ISABEL
No. But this view has been painted. A long time ago.
Panel 4
EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. VILLAGE STREETS.
SAUL
Who painted the view?
ISABEL
Someone my Grandmother knew.
SAUL
But that can't be right. It must have been 250 years ago.
Panel 5
ISABEL is looking at SAUL intently as they continue walking along the street. She is upset but is controlling it quietly.
Panel 6
ISABEL lays a hand on his arm as they walk. She is gentle.
ISABEL
Now, how would you know that?
</Text>
