        <Document ID="C376E019-466C-48A8-92C1-290DD2316A7C">
            <Title>Page 15: 1936</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. FOREST PATH. DEEP IN THE FOREST. GRANDMOTHER and the men are emerging from the forest. Before them can be seen agricultural fields and in the far distance the village can be seen on the top of the hill.

PANEL 2

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. EDGE OF THE FOREST. The men stand in a group looking at the village. The SERGEANT and EDWARD are standing by GRANDMOTHER.

SERGEANT
What kind of welcome will we get when we arrive?

GRANDMOTHER
What do you mean?

EDWARD
We fight for the left.

GRANDMOTHER
Left? Right? This is a thing for fools and historians. The rest of us? We hope for a good harvest and an inattentive God.

PANEL 3

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. FARM FIELDS. A PATH. The men walk through the fields. GRANDMOTHER is out front.

PANEL 4

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. VILLAGE OUTSKIRTS. THE STONE GATE. The men walk through the stone gates of the village. GRANDMOTHER is talking to one or two villagers who are standing by a cart and a donkey. They look nervous.

PANEL 5

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. VILLAGE STREETS. EDWARD and the SERGEANT are talking as they walk.

EDWARD
We been walking through these streets for hours. We're not getting anywhere.

SERGEANT
I'll speak to her.

PANEL 6

EXTERIOR: DAY. 1936. VILLAGE STREETS. The SERGEANT approaches GRANDMOTHER. He has his hands out to his sides.

GRANDMOTHER
I know. It is hard to force your way into this village. The forest does not want to let you go.

SERGEANT
What?

GRANDMOTHER
Calm yourself. We will reach the square by the morning.

</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="8E8D05F9-D0C6-4C2F-AC35-A5146427D67B">
            <Title>Page 21: 1936</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

Sergeant, Richard, Anbessa try to help those in church but are held back by the others and many of the villagers. Dissenting voices - the GM speaks up but is silenced. She is forced into the church along with S, R and A.</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="DD34A815-78B1-4CC3-A601-990F181EF667">
            <Title>Page 9: 2006</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

INTERIOR: 2006. NIGHT. SAUL &amp; KATES GARAGE. Its Christmas. The garage door is raised. SAUL stands in the dark just inside the open door. He is holding two bottles of wine by their necks.

PANEL 2

SAUL is looking through the wide window into his kitchen. KATE is standing in the kitchen talking to MARK.

PANEL 3

INTERIOR: 2006. NIGHT. SAUL &amp; KATES KITCHEN. KATE is talking gently to CHRISTOPHER - a friend from work. He has brought her a gift. It is in a small box and has a bow upon it. She has coyly laid a finger on his chest. It is too intimate for normal friends.

PANEL 4

INTERIOR: 2006. NIGHT. SAUL &amp; KATES KITCHEN. SAUL is coming through the kitchen door. KATE and  CHRISTOPHER are now standing apart. Nothing is obvious but something about the atmosphere is off - wrong. Each of them knows it.

PANEL 5

INTERIOR: 2006. NIGHT. SAUL &amp; KATES HALL. KATE and SAUL wave goodbye to CHRISTOPHER from the doorway of their home.  CHRISTOPHER drives away.

PANEL 6

SAUL and KATE look at each other blankly, as they stand in the doorway.
</Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="68F9D65E-6044-44F3-86D3-C0135D6ECE51">
            <Title>Page 6: 1936</Title>
            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

EXTERIOR: 1936. DAY. SUNNY. PYRENEES. BORDER CROSSING BETWEEN FRANCE AND SPAIN.

RICHARD
The Customs agent overcharged us you know.

EDWARD
I was too tired to argue. I suppose he has to make a living.

RICHARD
Not from my pocket.

PANEL 2

The two men walk across the International Bridge. There are twenty or more men heading towards the Spanish side of the border. The Pyranees mountains are a spectacular back-drop.

PANEL 3

Two men greet each entrant to Spain. One is in carabinero uniform. The other is wearing a dark blue boiler suit. He is a militiaman and has a luxuriant peasant mustache.

MILITIAMAN
Â¿Documentardo?

RICHARD
Yes.

MILITIAMAN
Ah... Â¿InglÃ©s?

EDWARD
SÂ¡. We have come to kill Fascists.

PANEL 4

The Militiaman smiles sardonically. It is not the first time today.

MILITIAMAN
En ese caso, la bienvenida a EspaÃ±a.

PANEL 5

The road down into the valley stretches out in front of them. Past the Militiaman you can see a panorama of yellow, green and orange fields, farm buildings and pearl grey villages. The mountains frame the picture on both sides. It is beautiful.

</Text>
