            <Text>PAGE &lt;$N&gt;

PANEL 1

EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. GRANDMOTHERS VINYARD. SAUL and ISABEL stand between a long row of vines. They are in a field of vines - long symetrical parallel rows.

SAUL
Why did you leave, Isabel?

ISABEL
To live. To learn and see something of the world.

PANEL 2

EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. SURROUNDING HILLS. SAUL and ISABEL are walking in  the hills around the vilage. We can see the village - on its own hill - in the background. SAUL and ISABEL are walking a dirt track - leading upwards.

SAUL
You intend to come back after your medical training?

ISABEL
Of course. I have roots in the soil.

PANEL 3

EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. FARM FIELD. SAUL and ISABEL are crossing a farmers field. The field is full of sheep. They are walking towards the village, which we can see - up on its hill - in the background.

SAUL
This would be a wonderful place to paint. Did I tell you I am an Art Historian?

ISABEL
No. But this view has been painted. A long time ago.

PANEL 4

EXTERIOR: 2013. DAY. VILLAGE STREETS.

SAUL
Who painted the view?

ISABEL
Someone my Grandmother knew.

SAUL
But that can't be right. It must have been 250 years ago.

PANEL 5

ISABEL is looking at SAUL intently as they continue walking along the street. She is upset but is controlling it quietly.

PANEL 6

ISABEL lays a hand on his arm as they walk. She is gentle.

ISABEL
Now, how would you know that?

</Text>
