CAP
As a cuckold I have dwindled, become clumsier and more brutal in my prejudices. My politics, crueller... "Sacrifices must be made", "Charity begins at home.", "We, after all, cannot help everyone".

CAP
I am unmanned and spiteful. I hate her and desire her. Salt in this open sore.

PANEL 6

INTERIOR: 2006. NIGHT. SAUL &amp; KATES BEDROOM.

CAP
Kate sleeps beside me, narrower, older somehow. Brimming with deceit and perfidy, poison held in the droplets of her breath.

PANEL 7

CAP
This sick terror, beating upon me like a rooks wings. The ghosts in this house only we can feel. She is leaving me. Even as she slumbers.
